@startuml

left to right direction

' === ACTORS ===
actor User as user
actor Scheduler as scheduler
actor TelegramBot as telegram
actor CarWizard as carwizard

' === MAIN USE CASE ===
(Search Vehicle On-Demand) as UC_MAIN

' === PRIMARY USE CASES ===
package "Search Orchestration" {
  (Parse Search Query) as UC1
  (Lookup FIPE Price) as UC2
  (Scrape OLX Listings) as UC3
  (Deduplicate Results) as UC4
}

package "Opportunity Processing" {
  (Compare Prices) as UC5
  (Calculate Opportunity Score) as UC6
  (Create/Update Opportunity) as UC7
}

package "Downstream Actions" {
  (Log to Google Sheets) as UC8
  (Send Telegram Alert) as UC9
  (Sync to CarWizard) as UC10
}

' === SUPPORTING USE CASES ===
(Cache FIPE Price) as UC11
(Validate Search Input) as UC12
(Format Search Query) as UC13
(Handle Errors) as UC14

' === ACTOR INTERACTIONS ===
user --> UC_MAIN : triggers search
UC_MAIN --> UC1 : includes
UC_MAIN --> UC2 : includes
UC_MAIN --> UC3 : includes
UC_MAIN --> UC5 : includes
UC_MAIN --> UC6 : includes
UC_MAIN --> UC7 : includes

' === USE CASE DEPENDENCIES ===

' Input validation
UC1 --> UC12 : uses
UC1 --> UC13 : uses

' FIPE Lookup
UC2 --> UC11 : <<include>>
UC2 --> UC14 : on failure

' OLX Scraping
UC3 --> UC4 : includes
UC3 --> UC14 : on failure

' Price Comparison
UC5 --> UC2 : requires FIPE price
UC5 --> UC3 : requires OLX listings

' Scoring
UC6 --> UC7 : creates opportunity

' Downstream Processing (conditional extensions)
UC7 --> UC8 : <<extend>> (all opportunities)
UC7 --> UC9 : <<extend>> (if score > 75)
UC7 --> UC10 : <<extend>> (if score > 80)

' Scheduler interactions for alerts
scheduler --> UC9 : processes queue
scheduler --> UC10 : processes sync queue

' External system interactions
telegram -.-> UC9 : receives alerts
carwizard -.-> UC10 : receives opportunity data

' === ERROR HANDLING ===
UC14 ..> UC2 : (FIPE API failure)
UC14 ..> UC3 : (OLX scraping failure)
UC14 ..> UC5 : (price comparison failure)
UC14 ..> UC6 : (scoring failure)

' === NOTES ===
note bottom of UC_MAIN
  **On-Demand Vehicle Search**
  User-initiated real-time search
  Reuses existing components:
  - FIPE lookup
  - OLX scraping (with search filter)
  - Scoring algorithm
  - Alert dispatch
end note

note right of UC1
  Normalize brand/model
  Validate inputs
  Handle variations (VW -> Volkswagen)
end note

note right of UC2
  Check 24-hour cache first
  Query FIPE API if missing
  Return reference price
end note

note right of UC3
  Use OLX scraper with search query
  Extract brand, model, year, price,
  mileage, condition, URL
end note

note right of UC5
  Calculate discount percentage
  Validate >20% threshold
  Flag suspicious discounts (>50%)
end note

note right of UC6
  Weighted scoring:
  - Discount: 40%
  - Condition: 30%
  - Demand: 20%
  - Recency: 10%
end note

note right of UC7
  Save to opportunities table
  Mark source as "on_demand_search"
  Update if duplicate URL
end note

note bottom of UC8
  Append to Google Sheets
  Include: vehicle, prices, discount,
  score, URL, timestamp, source
end note

note bottom of UC9
  Format Telegram message
  Queue for rate limiting
  Send if score > 75
end note

note bottom of UC10
  Send payload to CarWizard
  Include metadata
  Sync if score > 80
end note

note top of UC14
  **Error Handling:**
  - Log failures
  - Continue if possible
  - Notify user
  - Retry with backoff
end note

@enduml
